The paper deals with real-time systems, which are typically categorized under cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.EM (Embedded Systems). The paper also discusses scheduling and timing requirements, which are relevant to cs.RT (Real-Time and Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes protocols for transitioning between different modes of operation, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
